-- ESPN Gets Preliminary 12-Year Deal on College Football Playoffs
-- B y   C u r t i s   E i c h e l b e r g e r
-- 2012-11-21T18:16:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/espn-gets-preliminary-12-year-deal-on-college-football-playoffs.html
ESPN reached tentative agreement on
a 12-year media rights package for college football’s upcomng
championship playoff system, the  Walt Disney Co. (DIS)  unit said in a
news release.  Financial details weren’t disclosed. Sports Business
Journal reported that the deal is worth more than $7 billion,
citing people in the industry it didn’t identify.  ESPN said in the statement that the deal includes the
national championship and semifinal games, plus other,
unspecified postseason bowls. It starts after the 2014 regular
season and extends through January 2026, the sports cable outlet
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  